cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is about designing convolutional neural networks (CNN) for mobile devices, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes an automated approach for neural architecture search (NAS), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of real-world inference latency as a metric for evaluating the performance of mobile CNNs, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR).
